This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on training generative adversarial networks using different adversarial losses. It also involves the evaluation of different regularization approaches, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with the generation of images using GANs. 

The use of discriminative adversarial networks in the proposed framework suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The study of component functions and their effects on the adversarial loss may also fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of different loss functions, which may be considered as a topic in statistical learning theory (cs.SD).
